<div class="row">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Tutorial</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="span12">
      <ol>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">Download and install the addon from Mozilla's <%= link_to "addon website", "https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/trustauth/" %>.<%= image_tag "screen-1.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">Find the TrustAuth button (it looks like a beer glass) and click on it. Then click on login.<%= image_tag "screen-2.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">Since you just installed the addon, TrustAuth will ask you to create a master password. Remember this because it is required to unlock the addon later.<%= image_tag "screen-3.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">Now that you've created a password you can login to this demo site by clicking login again. After a few moments, TrustAuth will have finished generating your key and will log you into the site.<%= image_tag "screen-2.png", :class =>"trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">If this is your first time logging into this site, you will be prompted for an email address.<%= image_tag "screen-4.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">Now that you are logged in you can try leaving a note for yourself.<%= image_tag "screen-5.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">If the note was saved it should appear in your list.<%= image_tag "screen-6.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
        <li class="trustauth-tutorial-li">After you click logout, click login again and your note should be there!<%= image_tag "screen-7.png", :class => "trustauth-tutorial-img thumbnail" %></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
